                <note rend="inline" type="source">693.003/632: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ruddock</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-07-30T15:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 30, 1921—3 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>214. Your 256, July 12, noon.</p>
                <p>You may join representatives of other Treaty Powers in accepting proposal for a
                    conference to consider a revision of tariff schedules. Such revised tariff would
                    have eventually to be incorporated in a convention and submitted to the Senate
                    for ratification.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
